Pull the trigger, kick the stool, one final leap of faith; I can never just bring myself to take that extra (and last) step. I'm afraid. I'm afraid of what's always in store to come. If I live on, will my life get better? Or will it just further spiral into despair? If I were to die today, what awaits me afterwards? It's these very thoughts that keep me up at night. I dunno.
